<br>
Paladins are already one of the tanks of choice for experience groups, for those of us who still form pick up groups.  A well equipped Paladin brings much more to the table than an equally well equipped Warrior.  Which is kind of sad.  There should be some kind of parity, but there just isn't.  800-1k and defensive are meaningless in an experience group unless that group is truly pushing the envelope on what one group can accomplish.<br>
<br>
And Paladins have a real incentive to gain AAXP.  The benefits they gain are enough to get them over the hump of boss mob tanking.  A Warrior gets there with the right gear, so its easier for him.  But he has less incentive to work AAXP.  And if Paladins feel their class AAXP options aren't ideal, check out a Warrior's.  Other than AE taunt, the rest are pretty much considered cotton candy kind of additions.  Nice to have, but not really all that helpful.  Certainly not game changing.<br>
<br>
I do like some of your suggestions Maldrone, and its good to see that other people are begining to see and understand the issues.<br>
